/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=(), interest-cohort=()

# CSP is enforced via <meta> tag in BaseLayout.astro instead of a response
# header. Reason: Pagefind spawns a dedicated Web Worker that compiles WASM.
# When CSP is set as a response header, Chrome applies it to the worker's
# execution context too, blocking WebAssembly.instantiate() even with
# unsafe-eval. A <meta> CSP only applies to the document context and does
# not restrict workers, so Pagefind WASM loads cleanly.
# The pages.dev preview domain works because it has no CSP at all.
